<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-0232 </DOCNO><TEXT>The growing international interest in privatization of the power industryhas created opportunities for the private sector to develop new powerstations and related energy requirements. Privatization requires innovativeapproaches from project sponsors. One of these is build-own-transfer(BOT), in which the sponsors finance, build and operate the power station.Ownership is transferred back to the government after an agreed period,usually 10 to 15 years, at which time debt and equity have been repaid.BOT is expected to be used throughout the world, for coal-fired powerplants and other types of project too. It is essentially an installmentpurchase and so makes good sense for many developing countries. 2 figs.</TEXT></DOC>